cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with the problem of intrusion detection. The use of artificial immune systems and the Dendritic Cell Algorithm (DCA) also suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of multi-sensor data fusion and aggregate output analysis could also place it in the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the use of adaptive signals to alleviate false positives suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
